EQUINE ENCEPHALITIS - PANAMA (DARIEN)
*************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>
Date: Fri, 28 Aug 1998 02:11:26 -0500
From: Dr. Vicente Bayard <igorgas@sinfo.net>
Source: MINISTERIO DE SALUD DE PANAMA - INSTITUTO CONMEMORATIVO GORGAS
CENTRO DE CONTROL DE ENFERMEDADES
RESUMEN EJECUTIVO DE VIGILANCIA EPIDEMIOLOGICA ESPECIAL
808/CCE/19/08/98.Sem.Epidemiologica No. 32 (09/08/98-15/08/98) [Translated
by Mod.JW]

Executive Summary of Special Epidemiological Surveillance Epidemiological
Week No. 32 (9-15 Aug 1998)
An outbreak in horses in Chepigana, Darien. Laboratory results suggest
Eastern equine encephalitis.
[Original:
11.ENCEFALITIS EQUINA: Brote entre caballos de Chepigana, Darien.
Resultados de laboratorio sugieren encefalitis equina del este.]
--
Dr. Vicente Bayard
Director, Centro de Control de Enfermedades
INSTITUTO CONMEMORATIVO GORGAS DE ESTUDIOS DE LA SALUD
MINISTERIO DE SALUD DE PANAMA
e-mail: igorgas@sinfo.net
[Eastern equine encephalitis (EEE) is carried by mosquitoes. It is rarely
transmitted to man, when it can be fatal. Darien is the heavily forested
eastern end of Panama, bordering Colombia. The area of Colombia where
Venezuelan equine encephalitis has been reported (Casanare) is separated
from the Panama border by three mountain ranges, the Cordilleras. - Mod.JW]
